WEBVTT

1
00:00:21.962 --> 00:00:24.364
A very long time ago,

2
00:00:24.365 --> 00:00:27.234
there lived a beautiful Princess

3
00:00:27.235 --> 00:00:30.570
in a mystical land known as…

4
00:00:30.571 --> 00:00:32.306
India.

5
00:00:48.222 --> 00:00:52.259
She was married
to the handsome Prince Rama,


6
00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:55.395
who had been banished
to the enchanted forest


7
00:00:55.396 --> 00:00:59.600
by his jealous stepmother
Queen Kaikeyi.


8
00:01:08.276 --> 00:01:13.146
One day, Princess Sita saw
a wounded deer in the woods,


9
00:01:13.147 --> 00:01:16.350
and she begged Rama
to go and help it.


10
00:01:17.685 --> 00:01:20.887
Rama drew a circle in the ground

11
00:01:20.888 --> 00:01:22.289
and said to her,

12
00:01:22.290 --> 00:01:24.424
"this is a magic circle.

13
00:01:24.425 --> 00:01:26.359
"So long as you stay inside it,

14
00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:29.163
no harm can come to you."

15
00:01:32.566 --> 00:01:36.369
That night, the Princess
heard a horrible cry…


16
00:01:36.370 --> 00:01:38.771
"Aah! Help me!"

17
00:01:38.772 --> 00:01:41.574
Thinking it was
her beloved Rama in danger,


18
00:01:41.575 --> 00:01:44.177
the Princess ran from the circle

19
00:01:44.178 --> 00:01:46.180
to answer the cry.

20
00:01:54.255 --> 00:01:59.259
She soon came across
an old beggar man.


21
00:01:59.260 --> 00:02:02.128
Although she had
no money to give him,


22
00:02:02.129 --> 00:02:05.298
she could not refuse his plea.

23
00:02:05.299 --> 00:02:07.667
As soon as he had the bracelet,

24
00:02:07.668 --> 00:02:10.069
the beggar suddenly transformed

25
00:02:10.070 --> 00:02:12.672
into the 10-headed demon
Ravanna!


26
00:02:12.673 --> 00:02:15.775
He grabs the Princess
and takes her to his palace,


27
00:02:15.776 --> 00:02:19.512
where he intends
to make her his bride.


28
00:02:19.513 --> 00:02:22.114
Did you ever know
a real Prince, Maya?


29
00:02:22.115 --> 00:02:23.216
Yes…

30
00:02:23.217 --> 00:02:24.384
Laki's father.

31
00:02:24.385 --> 00:02:27.119
I thought he was in the army.

32
00:02:27.120 --> 00:02:28.154
He was,

33
00:02:28.155 --> 00:02:30.390
and he was my Prince,

34
00:02:30.391 --> 00:02:33.293
and I, his Princess.

35
00:02:33.294 --> 00:02:36.028
But I mean real princes
and princesses.


36
00:02:36.029 --> 00:02:38.298
All woman are princesses.

37
00:02:38.299 --> 00:02:40.233
It is our right.

38
00:03:21.742 --> 00:03:24.076
I shall miss it here.

39
00:03:24.077 --> 00:03:26.212
India's the only place on earth

40
00:03:26.213 --> 00:03:28.748
that stirs the imagination.

41
00:03:28.749 --> 00:03:31.685
I wish we could
stay here forever.


42
00:03:34.488 --> 00:03:36.356
I know, sweetheart,

43
00:03:36.357 --> 00:03:38.859
but now that England's
gone to war…


44
00:03:40.093 --> 00:03:41.761
I must go, too.

45
00:03:41.762 --> 00:03:43.696
You understand that, don't you?

46
00:03:43.697 --> 00:03:46.333
But why must I go to America?

47
00:03:46.334 --> 00:03:49.135
Because it's safer.
And besides,


48
00:03:49.136 --> 00:03:50.703
you'll be going
to the same school


49
00:03:50.704 --> 00:03:52.972
your mother went to
when she was your age,


50
00:03:52.973 --> 00:03:54.173
in a city called…

51
00:03:54.174 --> 00:03:55.174
New York.

52
00:03:55.175 --> 00:03:56.377
Mm-hmm.

53
00:04:00.981 --> 00:04:02.248
Papa?

54
00:04:02.249 --> 00:04:03.516
Mm-hmm?

55
00:04:03.517 --> 00:04:06.386
Maya told me that
all girls are princesses.


56
00:04:06.387 --> 00:04:08.388
Maya is a very wise woman.

57
00:04:08.389 --> 00:04:09.656
Then it's true?

58
00:04:09.657 --> 00:04:12.258
You can be anything you
want to be, my love,


59
00:04:12.259 --> 00:04:14.026
so long as you believe.

60
00:04:14.027 --> 00:04:15.662
What do you believe?

61
00:04:15.663 --> 00:04:17.430
I believe that you are

62
00:04:17.431 --> 00:04:21.702
and always will be
my little Princess.


63
00:04:59.840 --> 00:05:02.909
I gave this to your mother…

64
00:05:02.910 --> 00:05:04.911
on our wedding day.

65
00:05:04.912 --> 00:05:06.880
I want you to have it.

66
00:05:09.049 --> 00:05:12.052
She was so beautiful.

67
00:05:13.587 --> 00:05:17.323
What did you love
most about her?


68
00:05:17.324 --> 00:05:18.926
Tough question.

69
00:05:22.463 --> 00:05:26.198
I loved the way her eyes
lit up when she laughed…


70
00:05:26.199 --> 00:05:27.767
just like yours do.

71
00:05:27.768 --> 00:05:30.570
I loved the sound of her voice

72
00:05:30.571 --> 00:05:33.840
when she sang me
the Indian folk song.


73
00:05:33.841 --> 00:05:37.844
But I think…
more than anything else,


74
00:05:37.845 --> 00:05:40.648
I loved dancing with her!

75
00:05:49.356 --> 00:05:51.425
Ha ha ha!

76
00:06:54.287 --> 00:06:55.489
Hello!

77
00:06:56.289 --> 00:06:58.492
You must be Captain Crewe.

78
00:07:01.829 --> 00:07:04.130
My sister will be
down presently.


79
00:07:04.131 --> 00:07:05.565
We were just preparing

80
00:07:05.566 --> 00:07:07.166
the young lady's room.

81
00:07:07.167 --> 00:07:08.267
Your beautiful things

82
00:07:08.268 --> 00:07:09.268
arrived this morning.

83
00:07:09.269 --> 00:07:10.170
Thank you, uh…

84
00:07:10.171 --> 00:07:12.104
oh! Heavens…
Amelia.


85
00:07:12.105 --> 00:07:13.172
Amelia Minchin.

86
00:07:13.173 --> 00:07:14.440
Hee hee hee!

87
00:07:14.441 --> 00:07:17.778
Captain Crewe!

88
00:07:28.221 --> 00:07:31.158
How delightful to meet you.

89
00:07:33.393 --> 00:07:35.261
And this must be little Sara.

90
00:07:35.262 --> 00:07:37.797
My, what a beautiful child.

91
00:07:37.798 --> 00:07:39.065
I was just telling…

92
00:07:39.066 --> 00:07:41.400
thank you, Amelia.
That will be all.


93
00:07:41.401 --> 00:07:43.637
Now, won't you both follow me?

94
00:07:44.872 --> 00:07:47.807
Classes begin
promptly at 8:00.


95
00:07:47.808 --> 00:07:49.542
We cover all the subjects…

96
00:07:49.543 --> 00:07:51.410
literature, math, science,

97
00:07:51.411 --> 00:07:53.680
and, of course, both
French and Latin.


98
00:07:53.681 --> 00:07:54.947
Oh, well, Sara speaks fluent…

99
00:07:54.948 --> 00:07:56.949
luncheon is served
at 1:30,


100
00:07:56.950 --> 00:07:59.418
after which we take
our daily walk,


101
00:07:59.419 --> 00:08:00.519
unless, of course,

102
00:08:00.520 --> 00:08:02.021
the weather is
extremely inclement.


103
00:08:02.022 --> 00:08:02.956
From 4:00,

104
00:08:02.957 --> 00:08:05.692
the girls attend
classes in etiquette


105
00:08:05.693 --> 00:08:07.560
where they are
personally trained


106
00:08:07.561 --> 00:08:09.962
in all the formal
graces of society.


107
00:08:09.963 --> 00:08:10.764
Study hall

108
00:08:10.765 --> 00:08:13.265
is between

109
00:08:13.266 --> 00:08:14.934
followed by a light supper.

110
00:08:14.935 --> 00:08:16.402
And then, before bedtime,

111
00:08:16.403 --> 00:08:18.404
we read from
one of the classics,


112
00:08:18.405 --> 00:08:19.405
something the children

113
00:08:19.406 --> 00:08:20.539
always look forward to

114
00:08:20.540 --> 00:08:22.241
with great anticipation.

115
00:08:22.242 --> 00:08:23.442
Sunday is a day of rest.

116
00:08:23.443 --> 00:08:25.477
Students are allowed to
write only to their parents,


117
00:08:25.478 --> 00:08:27.379
and, of course,
we attend church.


118
00:08:27.380 --> 00:08:29.182
Have you any questions?

119
00:08:41.361 --> 00:08:42.930
Come along, dear.

120
00:08:50.203 --> 00:08:51.304
Ahem! Ahem!

121
00:08:52.339 --> 00:08:53.606
Oh, eh…

122
00:08:53.607 --> 00:08:54.741
Je mange…

123
00:08:54.742 --> 00:08:56.142
Tu mange…

124
00:08:56.143 --> 00:08:58.144
Excusez-moi,
monsieur DuFarge.


125
00:08:58.145 --> 00:09:01.213
Girls, I would like
you to say hello


126
00:09:01.214 --> 00:09:02.682
to our new arrival.

127
00:09:02.683 --> 00:09:04.316
Miss Sara Crewe.

128
00:09:04.317 --> 00:09:06.418
Hello, Sara.

129
00:09:06.419 --> 00:09:07.586
You must tell them

130
00:09:07.587 --> 00:09:09.756
all about your
exciting life in India.


131
00:09:09.757 --> 00:09:10.890
No doubt she'll be

132
00:09:10.891 --> 00:09:14.093
our most popular
student in no time.


133
00:09:14.094 --> 00:09:16.462
Now, there are certain rules

134
00:09:16.463 --> 00:09:18.497
that should be made quite clear.

135
00:09:18.498 --> 00:09:20.032
The first is the order rule,

136
00:09:20.033 --> 00:09:21.634
which requires the girls

137
00:09:21.635 --> 00:09:23.903
to keep their rooms
spotless at all times.


138
00:09:23.904 --> 00:09:25.905
Next is the kindness rule

139
00:09:25.906 --> 00:09:29.209
which teaches the girls…

140
00:09:51.098 --> 00:09:53.199
these rules are
strictly enforced,


141
00:09:53.200 --> 00:09:55.668
but I can assure
you, Captain Crewe,


142
00:09:55.669 --> 00:09:58.004
the results are well
worth the effort.


143
00:09:58.005 --> 00:10:00.072
Our reputation for sending

144
00:10:00.073 --> 00:10:03.810
the most poised and charming
young ladies into society


145
00:10:03.811 --> 00:10:06.813
is one of the highest.

146
00:10:06.814 --> 00:10:08.281
I've no doubt.

147
00:10:09.216 --> 00:10:13.686
Also, I'm afraid
jewelry and such finery


148
00:10:13.687 --> 00:10:14.687
are not allowed.

149
00:10:14.688 --> 00:10:16.288
What if I wear it in my room

150
00:10:16.289 --> 00:10:18.025
during my free time?

151
00:10:19.126 --> 00:10:22.029
Well, if you absolutely insist.

152
00:10:24.231 --> 00:10:25.698
I do.

153
00:10:27.567 --> 00:10:29.302
She's gonna get
in so much trouble.


154
00:10:34.541 --> 00:10:35.708
Monsieur?

155
00:10:35.709 --> 00:10:37.409
Je mange.

156
00:10:37.410 --> 00:10:38.677
Je mange.

157
00:10:38.678 --> 00:10:39.812
Tu mange.

158
00:10:39.813 --> 00:10:41.148
Tu mange.

159
00:10:45.318 --> 00:10:47.419
This is splendid.

160
00:10:47.420 --> 00:10:50.222
It's our largest suite.

161
00:10:50.223 --> 00:10:51.791
Thank you for all
the care you've taken,


162
00:10:51.792 --> 00:10:54.060
miss Minchin.
I want Sara to feel


163
00:10:54.061 --> 00:10:57.029
as much at home as
possible while I'm away.


164
00:10:57.030 --> 00:10:58.731
No expense should be spared.

165
00:10:58.732 --> 00:10:59.966
Of course not.

166
00:10:59.967 --> 00:11:02.568
Now, I'll let you two
say your good-byes.


167
00:11:02.569 --> 00:11:03.736
I know you don't have much time

168
00:11:03.737 --> 00:11:05.472
before your boat leaves.

169
00:11:20.153 --> 00:11:23.456
We'll write to
each other every day.


170
00:11:30.730 --> 00:11:32.731
How do you like your room?

171
00:11:32.732 --> 00:11:35.001
I made sure it was the best…

172
00:11:35.002 --> 00:11:38.470
corner windows and a fireplace.

173
00:11:38.471 --> 00:11:39.638
And with all your toys

174
00:11:39.639 --> 00:11:42.141
and clothes moved in, it's…

175
00:11:42.142 --> 00:11:44.812
it's just as if you were really…

176
00:11:47.614 --> 00:11:50.016
you know, I think
I saw something…


177
00:11:50.017 --> 00:11:52.219
on that chair over there.

178
00:11:56.023 --> 00:11:57.924
She came all the way from France

179
00:11:57.925 --> 00:11:59.993
just to be with you.

180
00:12:02.395 --> 00:12:05.065
Her name is Emily.

181
00:12:06.399 --> 00:12:07.835
Emily!

182
00:12:10.203 --> 00:12:14.006
You know, dolls make
the very best friends.


183
00:12:14.007 --> 00:12:16.242
Just because they can't speak

184
00:12:16.243 --> 00:12:18.878
doesn't mean they don't listen.

185
00:12:18.879 --> 00:12:20.246
And did you know

186
00:12:20.247 --> 00:12:22.681
that when we leave them
alone in our room,


187
00:12:22.682 --> 00:12:23.650
they come to life?

188
00:12:23.651 --> 00:12:25.084
They do?
Yes!


189
00:12:25.085 --> 00:12:27.053
But before we walk
in and catch them,


190
00:12:27.054 --> 00:12:28.387
they return to their places

191
00:12:28.388 --> 00:12:29.889
quick as lightning.

192
00:12:29.890 --> 00:12:31.924
Why don't they come
to life in front of us


193
00:12:31.925 --> 00:12:33.092
so we can see them?

194
00:12:33.093 --> 00:12:35.262
Because it's magic.

195
00:12:36.529 --> 00:12:38.297
Magic has to be believed.

196
00:12:38.298 --> 00:12:41.368
That's the only way it's real.

197
00:12:43.803 --> 00:12:45.771
Whenever you're afraid

198
00:12:45.772 --> 00:12:47.506
or miss me terribly,

199
00:12:47.507 --> 00:12:50.642
just tell Emily…

200
00:12:50.643 --> 00:12:52.278
and she'll get a message to me

201
00:12:52.279 --> 00:12:54.914
wherever I am,

202
00:12:54.915 --> 00:12:57.917
and then I'll send
one back right aways


203
00:12:57.918 --> 00:13:01.187
so that when you hug her,

204
00:13:01.188 --> 00:13:02.554
you'll really be getting

205
00:13:02.555 --> 00:13:04.424
a hug from me.

206
00:13:12.532 --> 00:13:15.135
It's all right, papa.

207
00:13:16.669 --> 00:13:19.506
I'm going to be fine.

208
00:13:27.547 --> 00:13:30.816
What are you doing?

209
00:13:30.817 --> 00:13:33.285
Memorizing me by heart?

210
00:13:33.286 --> 00:13:35.854
No.

211
00:13:35.855 --> 00:13:39.426
I already know you by heart.

212
00:13:59.146 --> 00:14:01.414
Good-bye, Princess.

213
00:14:32.279 --> 00:14:34.247
What were all those
noises last night?


214
00:14:36.916 --> 00:14:38.050
That's nothing.

215
00:14:38.051 --> 00:14:39.918
You should hear Josephine snore.

216
00:14:41.388 --> 00:14:42.222
I do not!

217
00:14:42.223 --> 00:14:45.191
Then who was it?
The new girl?


218
00:14:45.192 --> 00:14:47.926
She hasn't come
out of her room yet.


219
00:14:47.927 --> 00:14:49.928
Did you see all of her toys?

220
00:14:49.929 --> 00:14:51.463
I want your hair ribbon.

221
00:14:51.464 --> 00:14:53.665
Her father grows
crackers or something.


222
00:14:53.666 --> 00:14:55.667
They're very rich.

223
00:14:55.668 --> 00:14:56.702
They must be.

224
00:14:56.703 --> 00:14:58.537
Everyone I know eats crackers.

225
00:14:58.538 --> 00:14:59.705
Her father's British.

226
00:14:59.706 --> 00:15:02.208
I heard he's best friends
with the king and Queen.


227
00:15:02.209 --> 00:15:05.644
Hah! Well, I heard he
was thrown out of India


228
00:15:05.645 --> 00:15:06.546
because people died

229
00:15:06.547 --> 00:15:08.547
from eating his
poisoned crackers.


230
00:15:08.548 --> 00:15:10.082
Poisoned crackers.

231
00:15:10.083 --> 00:15:11.817
Poisoned crackers?

232
00:15:11.818 --> 00:15:13.219
I once had an aunt

233
00:15:13.220 --> 00:15:15.687
who died from eating
poisoned string beans.


234
00:15:15.688 --> 00:15:17.423
Oh, who cares about her?

235
00:15:17.424 --> 00:15:19.392
Yeah, who cares?

236
00:15:21.761 --> 00:15:24.630
But before we walk in
and catch them,


237
00:15:24.631 --> 00:15:27.534
they return to their places
quick as lightning.


238
00:15:28.568 --> 00:15:30.136
Gosh, she's fast.

239
00:15:42.515 --> 00:15:44.051
Mama.

240
00:15:45.852 --> 00:15:47.053
Sara.

241
00:15:47.054 --> 00:15:48.120
We're not accustomed

242
00:15:48.121 --> 00:15:49.056
to delaying everyone's breakfast

243
00:15:49.057 --> 00:15:50.222
for one student.

244
00:15:50.223 --> 00:15:51.390
I'm sorry, miss Minchin, but…

245
00:15:51.391 --> 00:15:53.225
you're not the only
child here, Sara.


246
00:15:53.226 --> 00:15:54.993
You must remember that.

247
00:15:54.994 --> 00:15:57.296
Ah, bonjour, monsieur dufarge.

248
00:15:57.297 --> 00:15:59.731
Comment d'etes vous aujourd'hui?

249
00:15:59.732 --> 00:16:01.867
Oh, yes, yes, yes.

250
00:16:01.868 --> 00:16:03.001
Good morning.

251
00:16:03.002 --> 00:16:04.603
I trust you remember
our newest pupil


252
00:16:04.604 --> 00:16:06.438
from our visit to
your class yesterday.


253
00:16:06.439 --> 00:16:08.640
Sara, this is monsieur dufarge.

254
00:16:08.641 --> 00:16:11.143
You begin French lessons
with him this afternoon.


255
00:16:11.144 --> 00:16:13.179
Do I have to?

256
00:16:13.180 --> 00:16:15.414
Sara! You most
certainly do.


257
00:16:15.415 --> 00:16:17.249
Now, apologize
to monsieur this instant


258
00:16:17.250 --> 00:16:18.550
for your rudeness.

259
00:16:18.551 --> 00:16:20.352
But I didn't mean to be rude.

260
00:16:20.353 --> 00:16:21.621
Now!

261
00:16:25.425 --> 00:16:28.026
Monsieur, je regrette,

262
00:16:28.027 --> 00:16:31.430
mais je sais parler francais.

263
00:16:31.431 --> 00:16:33.232
J'ai etudiá en inde
avec mon pére,


264
00:16:33.233 --> 00:16:34.400
qui habitait a Paris

265
00:16:34.401 --> 00:16:38.036
quand il átait un petit garçon.

266
00:16:38.037 --> 00:16:39.171
This child doesn't need

267
00:16:39.172 --> 00:16:40.439
to learn French.

268
00:16:40.440 --> 00:16:43.041
She practically is French.

269
00:16:43.042 --> 00:16:44.543
Says she learned it
from her father.


270
00:16:44.544 --> 00:16:47.913
I understood perfectly well
what she said, monsieur.


271
00:16:47.914 --> 00:16:49.315
I'm sorry, but we
tried to tell you.


272
00:16:49.316 --> 00:16:50.416
Well, perhaps she can

273
00:16:50.417 --> 00:16:51.950
tutor the younger children,

274
00:16:51.951 --> 00:16:53.719
and she might just
be able to help you


275
00:16:53.720 --> 00:16:57.323
with your pronunciation,
miss Minchin.


276
00:16:57.324 --> 00:17:00.392
Are those sausages I smell?

277
00:17:00.393 --> 00:17:01.394
Ohh!

278
00:17:14.674 --> 00:17:15.907
Thank you.

279
00:17:15.908 --> 00:17:16.975
Sara…

280
00:17:16.976 --> 00:17:19.378
there's no talking at the table.

281
00:17:19.379 --> 00:17:21.713
It doesn't seem natural.

282
00:17:24.317 --> 00:17:27.086
I won't say it again.

