325
00:20:01.508 --> 00:20:03.842
oh, please, lottie dear!

326
00:20:03.843 --> 00:20:05.977
Please stop screaming!

327
00:20:05.978 --> 00:20:07.513
Um, how about a cookie?

328
00:20:07.514 --> 00:20:08.980
Would you like that?

329
00:20:08.981 --> 00:20:10.382
Aah! Aaaah!

330
00:20:10.383 --> 00:20:12.451
I'll get a cookie.

331
00:20:12.452 --> 00:20:15.387
Aaaaah! Aaaaah!

332
00:20:15.388 --> 00:20:18.023
Aaaaaaaaaaah!

333
00:20:18.024 --> 00:20:20.526
Aaahhh! Aaahhh!

334
00:20:20.527 --> 00:20:21.693
You know, it's
very hard to study


335
00:20:21.694 --> 00:20:23.862
with you carrying on like this.

336
00:20:23.863 --> 00:20:25.130
I want my mama!

337
00:20:25.131 --> 00:20:26.598
You'll see her soon.

338
00:20:26.599 --> 00:20:28.534
No, I won't!
She's dead!


339
00:20:28.535 --> 00:20:30.802
And I won't ever see her again!

340
00:20:30.803 --> 00:20:34.341
Well, I don't have
a mother, either.


341
00:20:37.276 --> 00:20:39.011
You don't?

342
00:20:41.013 --> 00:20:42.314
Where is she?

343
00:20:42.315 --> 00:20:45.417
In heaven, with my baby sister,

344
00:20:45.418 --> 00:20:48.320
but that doesn't mean
I can't talk to her.


345
00:20:48.321 --> 00:20:52.290
I tell her everything,
and I know she hears me.


346
00:20:52.291 --> 00:20:54.426
How?

347
00:20:54.427 --> 00:20:56.695
Because that's what angels do.

348
00:20:56.696 --> 00:20:58.897
Your mama's an angel?

349
00:20:58.898 --> 00:21:00.031
Of course,

350
00:21:00.032 --> 00:21:01.433
and so is yours,

351
00:21:01.434 --> 00:21:04.202
with beautiful wings of silk

352
00:21:04.203 --> 00:21:06.438
and a crown of baby rosebuds.

353
00:21:06.439 --> 00:21:09.307
And they all live
together in a castle.


354
00:21:09.308 --> 00:21:12.177
And do you know
what it's made of?


355
00:21:12.178 --> 00:21:13.379
Sunflowers…

356
00:21:13.380 --> 00:21:14.846
hundreds of them…

357
00:21:14.847 --> 00:21:17.182
so bright they shine like gold.

358
00:21:18.385 --> 00:21:21.487
And when the angels want
to go someplace,


359
00:21:21.488 --> 00:21:23.188
they just whistle like this.

360
00:21:31.531 --> 00:21:33.365
And a cloud floats
to the castle door


361
00:21:33.366 --> 00:21:35.467
and picks them up,

362
00:21:35.468 --> 00:21:37.769
and as the angels
fly through the sky,


363
00:21:37.770 --> 00:21:41.407
riding the cloud
like a magic carpet,


364
00:21:41.408 --> 00:21:45.077
under the moon and
through the stars…


365
00:21:48.615 --> 00:21:52.885
until they're hovering
right above us.


366
00:21:54.721 --> 00:21:55.787
That's how they can look down

367
00:21:55.788 --> 00:21:59.625
and see if we're all right.

368
00:21:59.626 --> 00:22:03.062
And sometimes they even
send messages to us.


369
00:22:04.631 --> 00:22:08.166
Of course, you can't
hear the messages


370
00:22:08.167 --> 00:22:09.601
if you're kicking and screaming

371
00:22:09.602 --> 00:22:11.103
as loudly as you were…

372
00:22:12.371 --> 00:22:14.873
but they always try again,

373
00:22:14.874 --> 00:22:16.842
just in case we've missed it.

374
00:22:20.012 --> 00:22:22.113
Hey, wait.

375
00:22:22.114 --> 00:22:23.549
That's Becky.

376
00:22:23.550 --> 00:22:25.717
She's not allowed to talk to us.

377
00:22:25.718 --> 00:22:26.718
Why not?

378
00:22:26.719 --> 00:22:28.454
She's a servant girl,

379
00:22:28.455 --> 00:22:30.922
and she has dark skin.

380
00:22:30.923 --> 00:22:31.990
So?

381
00:22:31.991 --> 00:22:35.928
Well, doesn't that
mean something?


382
00:23:20.106 --> 00:23:21.139
I'm sorry. I…

383
00:23:21.140 --> 00:23:24.042
is there anything
I can do for you, miss?


384
00:23:24.043 --> 00:23:26.778
I just came up here
to change my shoes.


385
00:23:26.779 --> 00:23:29.380
No. No,
there's nothing.


386
00:23:29.381 --> 00:23:31.650
Well, then, begging your pardon,

387
00:23:31.651 --> 00:23:34.986
but we'll both be
in trouble if you stay.


388
00:23:39.659 --> 00:23:42.862
All right, girls.
Pair up.


389
00:23:44.864 --> 00:23:46.599
Pair up.

390
00:24:37.216 --> 00:24:40.952
"Sir Edward saw the sorrow
in his daughter's eyes,"


391
00:24:40.953 --> 00:24:43.555
"but he knew that
family honor must prevail"


392
00:24:43.556 --> 00:24:44.890
"at all costs."

393
00:24:44.891 --> 00:24:47.693
"Nobility was not a thing
to be trifled with."


394
00:24:47.694 --> 00:24:50.629
"I beg of you, Charlotte,
he said,"


395
00:24:50.630 --> 00:24:52.463
marry Sir John in the spring

396
00:24:52.464 --> 00:24:54.232
"as he has asked."

397
00:24:54.233 --> 00:24:55.901
Thank you, lavinia.

398
00:24:55.902 --> 00:24:58.705
Sara, you may take your turn.

399
00:25:09.081 --> 00:25:10.816
"Charlotte turned to her father

400
00:25:10.817 --> 00:25:13.018
"and said,
father, you are right.


401
00:25:13.019 --> 00:25:15.553
"I must put away
my foolish fancies


402
00:25:15.554 --> 00:25:17.023
and childhood wishes."

403
00:25:26.733 --> 00:25:29.200
"But I simply won't do it.

404
00:25:29.201 --> 00:25:30.769
"I'm sorry, father,

405
00:25:30.770 --> 00:25:32.804
but when I marry,
it will be for love."


406
00:25:32.805 --> 00:25:36.541
And with that, Charlotte
ran from the house.


407
00:25:36.542 --> 00:25:37.843
Waiting outside for her

408
00:25:37.844 --> 00:25:39.611
was the handsome stable boy
Pierre,


409
00:25:39.612 --> 00:25:41.613
whom Charlotte secretly adored.

410
00:25:41.614 --> 00:25:43.615
Together
they escaped to the coast


411
00:25:43.616 --> 00:25:46.618
and quickly set sail
for the island of Tahiti.


412
00:25:46.619 --> 00:25:48.286
But when they were
halfway there,


413
00:25:48.287 --> 00:25:51.790
their ship was attacked
by a band of pirates.


414
00:25:51.791 --> 00:25:53.625
Rather than be eaten alive,

415
00:25:53.626 --> 00:25:54.760
Charlotte and Pierre

416
00:25:54.761 --> 00:25:57.495
threw themselves
into the raging sea.


417
00:25:57.496 --> 00:25:59.364
And as they began to drown,

418
00:25:59.365 --> 00:26:01.132
they held each other close

419
00:26:01.133 --> 00:26:02.768
and swore their undying love.

420
00:26:05.138 --> 00:26:07.272
But then, when all seemed lost,

421
00:26:07.273 --> 00:26:09.675
a group of mermaids
appeared and rescued…


422
00:26:09.676 --> 00:26:10.877
stop!

423
00:26:15.547 --> 00:26:17.348
What are you doing?

424
00:26:17.349 --> 00:26:20.952
I couldn't bear to see
Charlotte marry that awful man,


425
00:26:20.953 --> 00:26:22.721
so I imagined
a different ending.


426
00:26:22.722 --> 00:26:24.156
You imagined it.

427
00:26:24.991 --> 00:26:27.693
Don't you ever do that,
miss Minchin?


428
00:26:27.694 --> 00:26:31.297
Believe in something
just to make it seem real?


429
00:26:33.565 --> 00:26:34.966
I suppose that's rather easy

430
00:26:34.967 --> 00:26:37.168
for a child who has everything.

431
00:26:37.169 --> 00:26:38.336
But from now on,

432
00:26:38.337 --> 00:26:40.972
there will be no more
make-believe at this school


433
00:26:40.973 --> 00:26:43.474
during reading hour
or at any other time!


434
00:26:43.475 --> 00:26:44.876
Is that understood?

435
00:26:44.877 --> 00:26:46.812
Yes, miss Minchin.

436
00:26:46.813 --> 00:26:49.181
Now, all of you, go to
your bed this instant.


437
00:26:53.485 --> 00:26:55.754
I never heard a story like that

438
00:26:55.755 --> 00:26:57.155
in my whole life.

439
00:26:57.156 --> 00:26:59.624
I bet you know lots of them,

440
00:26:59.625 --> 00:27:01.026
don't you, Sara?

441
00:27:01.027 --> 00:27:03.963
I want silence up there!

442
00:27:04.897 --> 00:27:06.564
We have to do something

443
00:27:06.565 --> 00:27:09.067
about this communication rule.

444
00:27:09.068 --> 00:27:11.803
Hey, after Minchin goes to bed,

445
00:27:11.804 --> 00:27:13.204
we'll sneak into your room,

446
00:27:13.205 --> 00:27:16.674
and you can show us
what a real story is.


447
00:27:16.675 --> 00:27:17.943
How about it, Sara?

448
00:27:17.944 --> 00:27:20.411
Well, only if it's
just you three.


449
00:27:20.412 --> 00:27:22.547
Colleen, wait for me.

450
00:27:22.548 --> 00:27:23.750
Shh!

451
00:27:43.602 --> 00:27:45.371
Come on, come on.

452
00:28:08.861 --> 00:28:10.295
The evil Ravanna

453
00:28:10.296 --> 00:28:13.164
locked the Princess up
in his palace tower.


454
00:28:13.165 --> 00:28:15.901
There she stayed for many weeks,

455
00:28:15.902 --> 00:28:18.036
just staring out her window,

456
00:28:18.037 --> 00:28:21.107
missing her Prince Rama
terribly.


457
00:28:28.680 --> 00:28:30.348
Bonjour, papa.

458
00:28:30.349 --> 00:28:33.551
Je suis trés contente
de vous voir.


459
00:28:33.552 --> 00:28:34.820
Bonjour, papa.

460
00:28:34.821 --> 00:28:38.290
Je suis trés contente
de vous voir.


461
00:28:39.792 --> 00:28:41.692
Perfect.

462
00:28:41.693 --> 00:28:44.030
You look just like Emily.

463
00:28:45.564 --> 00:28:47.698
My father hates dolls,

464
00:28:47.699 --> 00:28:49.835
and he hates coming here.

465
00:28:49.836 --> 00:28:52.237
Says he doesn't belong.

466
00:28:52.238 --> 00:28:54.840
Then why does he send you?

467
00:28:54.841 --> 00:28:57.742
'Cause he wants me to belong.

468
00:29:27.273 --> 00:29:31.476
My little girl,
she spoke French!


469
00:29:31.477 --> 00:29:34.046
She really spoke French.

470
00:29:35.747 --> 00:29:38.050
Your mother and I
are very proud of you.


471
00:29:41.387 --> 00:29:42.487
Hello, sweetheart.

472
00:29:42.488 --> 00:29:43.688
Hi.

473
00:29:43.689 --> 00:29:45.823
Hi.

474
00:29:45.824 --> 00:29:49.395
I caught you, Debbie.

475
00:29:51.030 --> 00:29:54.100
Oh, you look so pretty…

476
00:30:13.819 --> 00:30:15.187
papa!

477
00:30:50.789 --> 00:30:53.525
Oh.

478
00:31:05.271 --> 00:31:06.471
Randolph?

479
00:31:06.472 --> 00:31:07.473
John!

480
00:31:10.909 --> 00:31:14.145
Rama approached
the thorny palace…


481
00:31:14.146 --> 00:31:17.248
unaware that Ravanna
was waiting for him.


482
00:31:17.249 --> 00:31:18.883
Oh!

483
00:31:18.884 --> 00:31:20.086
Why?

484
00:31:27.759 --> 00:31:29.794
That's it!

485
00:31:29.795 --> 00:31:31.129
I can't take it anymore.

486
00:31:31.130 --> 00:31:33.564
I don't care what you say
about Sara's stories.


487
00:31:33.565 --> 00:31:34.565
They've got to be more fun

488
00:31:34.566 --> 00:31:36.502
than watching
your hair being combed.


489
00:31:38.104 --> 00:31:40.305
If anyone else
feels the same way,


490
00:31:40.306 --> 00:31:42.408
I think she should leave, too.

491
00:31:51.217 --> 00:31:52.984
Come on, come on.

492
00:31:52.985 --> 00:31:54.553
Shh.

493
00:31:57.056 --> 00:31:59.957
But the evil Ravanna
was not through yet.


494
00:31:59.958 --> 00:32:02.093
This time he took a bow

495
00:32:02.094 --> 00:32:05.063
that could hold not 1,
but 10 arrows,


496
00:32:05.064 --> 00:32:07.298
each filled
with a deadly poison.


497
00:32:07.299 --> 00:32:09.834
The arrows sped through the air,

498
00:32:09.835 --> 00:32:11.902
heading straight for Rama.

499
00:32:11.903 --> 00:32:14.372
And the arrows hit the ground

500
00:32:14.373 --> 00:32:16.107
and released their poison,

501
00:32:16.108 --> 00:32:20.712
giant clouds of thick,
yellow smoke.


502
00:32:57.049 --> 00:32:58.049
Unh.

503
00:33:26.145 --> 00:33:28.045
I want a big piece!

504
00:33:28.046 --> 00:33:29.447
Oh, hush up, lottie.

505
00:33:29.448 --> 00:33:31.048
I'm sure Princess Sara

506
00:33:31.049 --> 00:33:33.151
