run away together


926
01:05:51.055 --> 01:05:52.121
and get married.

927
01:05:52.122 --> 01:05:55.858
It would be terribly romantic.

928
01:05:55.859 --> 01:05:59.428
What an extraordinary
thing to say.


929
01:05:59.429 --> 01:06:01.597
I…

930
01:06:01.598 --> 01:06:02.798
I…

931
01:06:02.799 --> 01:06:04.400
I…

932
01:06:04.401 --> 01:06:05.469
I…

933
01:06:07.104 --> 01:06:09.405
Well, anyway…

934
01:06:09.406 --> 01:06:11.707
my sister would be furious
if she found out.


935
01:06:11.708 --> 01:06:12.708
So?

936
01:06:12.709 --> 01:06:15.111
You'd be long gone by then,

937
01:06:15.112 --> 01:06:17.880
living in some exotic paradise…

938
01:06:17.881 --> 01:06:20.383
with that dashing young milkman.

939
01:06:20.384 --> 01:06:22.151
Ohh.

940
01:06:22.152 --> 01:06:25.354
Well, I'd better get
to the market.


941
01:06:25.355 --> 01:06:26.423
Ohh.

942
01:06:32.329 --> 01:06:33.330
Ohh.

943
01:06:47.010 --> 01:06:49.578
You're doing well, young man.

944
01:06:49.579 --> 01:06:51.148
You're almost home.

945
01:06:53.417 --> 01:06:56.620
You must trust my eyes, sahib.

946
01:07:17.974 --> 01:07:19.576
Shh.

947
01:07:24.814 --> 01:07:26.282
What's going on?

948
01:07:26.283 --> 01:07:28.118
It's a surprise.

949
01:07:32.322 --> 01:07:34.357
What are you doing here?

950
01:07:34.358 --> 01:07:36.160
We brought you something.

951
01:07:40.330 --> 01:07:41.697
Princess Sara…

952
01:07:41.698 --> 01:07:44.200
we'd like to present you
with something we rescued.


953
01:07:44.201 --> 01:07:46.702
In a most dangerous adventure.

954
01:07:46.703 --> 01:07:48.003
Our very own crusade.

955
01:07:48.004 --> 01:07:49.938
Risking all our lives.

956
01:07:49.939 --> 01:07:52.142
And mine, too.

957
01:07:58.047 --> 01:07:59.315
I…

958
01:07:59.316 --> 01:08:02.186
I don't know what to say.

959
01:08:04.754 --> 01:08:09.225
You all are the best friends
anyone could ever ask for.


960
01:08:09.226 --> 01:08:12.127
Aah!
Aah!


961
01:08:12.128 --> 01:08:13.762
It's all right.

962
01:08:13.763 --> 01:08:18.033
That's just my little
monkey friend hanuman.


963
01:08:18.034 --> 01:08:20.836
Where did he come from?

964
01:08:20.837 --> 01:08:22.771
Right next door.
Look.


965
01:08:22.772 --> 01:08:26.175
Hanuman likes to come
and visit me all the time.


966
01:08:26.176 --> 01:08:28.711
Can you really
talk to him, Sara?


967
01:08:28.712 --> 01:08:29.646
Sure.

968
01:08:29.647 --> 01:08:32.548
Hanuman, say hello
to all my friends.


969
01:08:54.304 --> 01:08:56.605
After Rama came back to life,

970
01:08:56.606 --> 01:09:00.209
he raced on toward
the monster's palace


971
01:09:00.210 --> 01:09:01.977
to rescue Sita, but suddenly…

972
01:09:03.079 --> 01:09:06.014
Ravanna appeared.

973
01:09:06.015 --> 01:09:09.184
Aah!
Aah!


974
01:09:18.695 --> 01:09:22.665
I think we better save
the rest of the story


975
01:09:22.666 --> 01:09:23.767
for later.

976
01:09:35.912 --> 01:09:38.382
Hee hee hee.
Hee hee hee.


977
01:09:41.318 --> 01:09:43.218
What's going on here?

978
01:09:43.219 --> 01:09:46.021
It's not their fault.
I asked them to come.


979
01:09:46.022 --> 01:09:47.022
You five get downstairs

980
01:09:47.023 --> 01:09:48.056
immediately.

981
01:09:48.057 --> 01:09:49.826
I'll deal with you later.

982
01:09:51.027 --> 01:09:52.160
Becky…

983
01:09:52.161 --> 01:09:53.662
you will remain
locked in your room


984
01:09:53.663 --> 01:09:54.963
for the entire day tomorrow,

985
01:09:54.964 --> 01:09:56.665
without meals.

986
01:09:56.666 --> 01:09:57.667
Go!

987
01:10:00.203 --> 01:10:03.138
And you will perform
all her chores


988
01:10:03.139 --> 01:10:04.273
in addition to your own

989
01:10:04.274 --> 01:10:07.075
without breakfast,
lunch, or dinner.


990
01:10:07.076 --> 01:10:08.677
It's time you learn, Sara Crewe,

991
01:10:08.678 --> 01:10:10.479
that real life has nothing to do

992
01:10:10.480 --> 01:10:12.681
with your little fantasy games.

993
01:10:12.682 --> 01:10:15.284
It's a cruel, nasty
world out there,


994
01:10:15.285 --> 01:10:17.620
and it's our duty to
make the best of it,


995
01:10:17.621 --> 01:10:21.223
not to indulge in
ridiculous dreams,


996
01:10:21.224 --> 01:10:24.328
but to be productive and useful.

997
01:10:27.297 --> 01:10:30.567
Do you understand
what I'm saying?


998
01:10:32.836 --> 01:10:34.438
Yes, ma'am.

999
01:10:36.573 --> 01:10:37.607
Good.

1000
01:10:39.976 --> 01:10:42.011
But I don't believe in it.

1001
01:10:45.982 --> 01:10:46.916
Don't tell me

1002
01:10:46.917 --> 01:10:49.585
you still fancy
yourself a Princess!


1003
01:10:49.586 --> 01:10:50.454
Ha ha!

1004
01:10:50.455 --> 01:10:52.287
Good god, child,
look around you.


1005
01:10:52.288 --> 01:10:53.889
Or better yet,

1006
01:10:53.890 --> 01:10:55.792
look in the mirror.

1007
01:11:02.432 --> 01:11:05.067
I am a Princess.

1008
01:11:05.068 --> 01:11:06.835
All girls are…

1009
01:11:06.836 --> 01:11:10.172
even if they live
in tiny old attics,


1010
01:11:10.173 --> 01:11:13.241
even if they dress in rags,

1011
01:11:13.242 --> 01:11:14.810
even if they aren't pretty

1012
01:11:14.811 --> 01:11:17.079
or smart or young,

1013
01:11:17.080 --> 01:11:19.448
they're still princesses,

1014
01:11:19.449 --> 01:11:20.849
all of us.

1015
01:11:20.850 --> 01:11:24.887
Didn't your father
ever tell you that?


1016
01:11:24.888 --> 01:11:26.823
Didn't he?

1017
01:11:30.927 --> 01:11:32.260
If I find you up here

1018
01:11:32.261 --> 01:11:33.729
with any of the girls again,

1019
01:11:33.730 --> 01:11:36.332
I will throw you out
into the street!


1020
01:12:09.433 --> 01:12:11.534
What are we going to do?

1021
01:12:11.535 --> 01:12:15.370
A whole day with nothing to eat.

1022
01:12:15.371 --> 01:12:17.973
Don't cry, Becky.

1023
01:12:17.974 --> 01:12:19.508
I'm scared.

1024
01:12:19.509 --> 01:12:21.376
If Minchin throws me out,

1025
01:12:21.377 --> 01:12:23.412
I got no place to go.

1026
01:12:23.413 --> 01:12:26.214
That's not true.

1027
01:12:26.215 --> 01:12:28.050
I'm here with you.

1028
01:12:28.051 --> 01:12:31.286
I've always thought
of us as sisters.


1029
01:12:31.287 --> 01:12:32.788
You have?

1030
01:12:32.789 --> 01:12:35.257
Let's make a promise right now

1031
01:12:35.258 --> 01:12:37.125
to always look out
for each other.


1032
01:12:37.126 --> 01:12:38.595
It's a promise.

1033
01:12:40.997 --> 01:12:44.500
Now, what are we going
to do about food?


1034
01:12:44.501 --> 01:12:46.368
Starve, I guess.

1035
01:12:46.369 --> 01:12:50.338
No. There's only
one thing to do.


1036
01:12:50.339 --> 01:12:51.807
We'll eat a great feast

1037
01:12:51.808 --> 01:12:53.375
before we go to sleep,

1038
01:12:53.376 --> 01:12:55.210
and that will keep us full

1039
01:12:55.211 --> 01:12:56.411
all day tomorrow.

1040
01:12:56.412 --> 01:12:58.180
Feast?

1041
01:12:58.181 --> 01:12:59.448
What feast?

1042
01:12:59.449 --> 01:13:01.650
Just look around.

1043
01:13:01.651 --> 01:13:04.620
Do you see that table
over there?


1044
01:13:04.621 --> 01:13:07.490
It's covered with
a beautiful cloth


1045
01:13:07.491 --> 01:13:08.891
and candles

1046
01:13:08.892 --> 01:13:12.161
and trays and trays
of good things to eat.


1047
01:13:13.296 --> 01:13:15.063
Come on, Becky.

1048
01:13:15.064 --> 01:13:17.566
Tell me what kind
of food there is.


1049
01:13:17.567 --> 01:13:21.570
But I don't see any food.

1050
01:13:21.571 --> 01:13:23.572
Try, Becky.

1051
01:13:23.573 --> 01:13:25.574
Just make believe it.

1052
01:13:25.575 --> 01:13:29.779
Remember what you told
me about the magic?


1053
01:13:38.788 --> 01:13:40.088
Muffins?

1054
01:13:40.089 --> 01:13:42.224
Good! What kind?

1055
01:13:42.225 --> 01:13:43.626
All kinds…

1056
01:13:43.627 --> 01:13:46.629
every kind of muffin
god ever made,


1057
01:13:46.630 --> 01:13:48.831
and all of them hot.

1058
01:13:48.832 --> 01:13:49.966
Good!

1059
01:13:51.467 --> 01:13:52.467
Oh.

1060
01:13:52.468 --> 01:13:53.869
We're not dressed right

1061
01:13:53.870 --> 01:13:56.472
for such an elegant banquet.

1062
01:13:58.341 --> 01:14:01.844
I'm wearing a long, velvet cape

1063
01:14:01.845 --> 01:14:03.979
with fur on the collar.

1064
01:14:03.980 --> 01:14:05.047
How 'bout you?

1065
01:14:05.048 --> 01:14:08.216
Well, I always liked
diamonds myself…


1066
01:14:08.217 --> 01:14:09.552
rings and bracelets

1067
01:14:09.553 --> 01:14:11.954
and a whole dress
just covered with them.


1068
01:14:11.955 --> 01:14:13.922
Ha ha ha ha.

1069
01:14:13.923 --> 01:14:15.090
Mmm.

1070
01:14:15.091 --> 01:14:17.560
Smell those sausages.

1071
01:14:17.561 --> 01:14:19.361
Oh, I love sausages.

1072
01:14:58.501 --> 01:14:59.903
Mmm.

1073
01:15:33.903 --> 01:15:35.171
Ohh!

1074
01:15:37.607 --> 01:15:40.777
Mmm.

1075
01:15:44.313 --> 01:15:45.447
Becky!

1076
01:15:45.448 --> 01:15:46.650
Becky!

1077
01:15:50.754 --> 01:15:52.656
Oh, my lord.

1078
01:15:54.390 --> 01:15:56.725
I think you went
a little too far


1079
01:15:56.726 --> 01:15:57.760
this time.

1080
01:15:57.761 --> 01:15:59.595
It wasn't me.

1081
01:16:04.367 --> 01:16:05.702
Go ahead.

1082
01:16:18.782 --> 01:16:22.384
I feel like I've been
touched by an angel.


1083
01:16:22.385 --> 01:16:23.385
And look…

1084
01:16:23.386 --> 01:16:25.553
just what we ordered.

1085
01:16:25.554 --> 01:16:28.490
I'm a little scared
about all of this.


1086
01:16:28.491 --> 01:16:30.525
Me, too.

1087
01:16:30.526 --> 01:16:31.894
You think we shouldn't eat it?

1088
01:16:31.895 --> 01:16:33.797
I'm not that scared.

1089
01:16:45.975 --> 01:16:48.576
Thank you for all your kindness.

1090
01:16:48.577 --> 01:16:50.545
I'm so sorry
to inconvenience you.


1091
01:16:50.546 --> 01:16:52.181
It is nothing, sahib.

1092
01:16:58.087 --> 01:16:59.222
That word…

1093
01:17:01.390 --> 01:17:03.058
it sounds so familiar,

1094
01:17:03.059 --> 01:17:06.661
